If I serve not him, I will run as far as God has any ground.—O rare fortune!
Here comes the man.—To him, Father, for I am a Jew if I serve the Jew any longer.
To him, Father.
Gramercy!
Wouldst thou aught with me?
Here’s my son, sir, a poor boy— Not a poor boy, sir, but the rich Jew’s man that would, sir, as my father shall specify—  He hath a great infection, sir, as one would say, to serve— Indeed the short and the long is, I serve the Jew and have a desire, as my father shall specify— 
